Steps to create a website using minimal mistakes academic pages (github/jekyll)

1. Install homebrew (package manager for mac) 
2. Install rbenv (and follow all steps for Ruby from here: https://gorails.com/setup/osx/10.13-high-sierra)
3. Clone the github folder locally
4. Go to the github folder in terminal
5. Run the instructions which are on the minimal mistakes instructions ("To run locally")

Running local server:
bundle exec jekyll liveserve
